<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>

    <!--
      This is the main Handlebars template for the site
      - When the user visits the homepage or submits a color the app calls the endpoints in server.js
      - The server script passes data in here and the Handlebars code builds it into the HTML page
    -->

    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

    <title>{{title}}</title>

    <!-- Import the webpage's stylesheet -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
	<script>
		function checkAccess() {
			// The `host` string here is replaced by the domain (the value in the URL bar of your browser) you are using to access this file by the server.
			if ('localhost:3000' === '{{host}}'){
				var solutionDiv = document.getElementById('domain-check')
				solutionDiv.style.backgroundColor = "lightgreen"
				solutionDiv.innerText = "You are accessing the project on the right domain"
			} else {
				var solutionDiv = document.getElementById('domain-check')
				solutionDiv.style.backgroundColor = "pink"
				solutionDiv.innerText = "You are accessing the project on the wrong domain"
			}
		}
		checkAccess()
	</script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="content" role="main">

        <!-- This is the start of content for our page -->
        <h1 class="title">Hello!</h1>
        <p>
          {{someText}}
        </p>

    </div>

        <div class="illo-container">
          <img src="https://cdn.glitch.com/c62efef6-1e75-45cf-b248-afeccdda9477%2Fillustration.svg?v=1618196069568" class="illustration" alt="Node logo" />
        </div>

        <!-- Instructions on using this project -->
        <div class="instructions">
			<h2>
				Welcome to the test!
			</h2>
			<p>
				This is the first page of the project. If you're seeing this, you are on your way! This page has a function in the `HEAD` that checks to make sure you are accessing the site on the right domain and verifies it by writing a message into the paragraph tag below. It does not currently work.
			</p>

			<p>
				Here we're checking your proficiency with handling the order of the browser's parsing of an HTML document. To complete this test you must get the `checkAccess` function working in place, without moving the function into a script file or moving the script tag from the `HEAD` area.
			</p>
			<p id="domain-check"></p>
			<p>
				Once you have completed this test, the next test is the at <a href="/frame-page">the iframe page</a>
			</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
